      "content": "Substantive due process is a crucial legal doctrine that protects fundamental rights from government overreach, ensuring the government can't infringe on deeply held liberties. It has been instrumental in expanding civil rights by striking down laws that infringe upon personal autonomy, such as those related to privacy and bodily integrity. This concept allows the courts to safeguard individual freedoms against legislative encroachment, which is a cornerstone of a free society.",
